{{Infobox Journal | title = Dumbarton Oaks Papers | cover = Dumbarton Oaks Papers cover.gif | editor = | discipline = [[Byzantine art]] and [[medieval art]] | language = [[English language|English]] | abbreviation = Dumbarton Oaks Pap. | publisher = [[Dumbarton Oaks]] | country = [[United States of America|USA]] | frequency = | history = 1941- | openaccess = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.doaks.org/resources/publications/dumbarton-oaks-papers | link1 = https://web.archive.org/web/20070929092320/http://www.doaks.org/etexts.html | link1-name = etexts | link2 = | link2-name = | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = 00707546 | OCLC = 58423962 | LCCN = 2005236610 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0070-7546 | eISSN = }}
'''Dumbarton Oaks Papers''' (DOP) is an academic journal founded in 1941 for the publication of articles relating to civilizations of the [[Ancient history|late antique]], [[Early Middle Ages|early medieval]], and [[Byzantine Empire|Byzantine]] periods.
Publication was suspended during World War II, resuming in 1946 irregularly at first, and eventually published annually by the mid-1950s.
