{{refimprove|date=November 2017}} {{Infobox software | name = Praat | logo = Praat icon.png | screenshot = Spectrogram - motángo mwa basodá.png | caption = | developer = Paul Boersma and David Weenink, from the Institute of Phonetic Sciences - [[University of Amsterdam]]. | released = ? | programming language = [[C (programming language)|C]], [[C++]] | operating system = [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Linux]], [[Macintosh]], [[FreeBSD]], [[Solaris (operating system)|Solaris]] | language = English | genre = [[Free software]] | license = [[GNU GPL]] | website = [http://www.praat.org/ www.praat.org/] }}
'''Praat''' ({{IPAc-en|p|r|ɑː|t}}; {{IPA-nl|praːt|lang|Nl-praat.ogg}}, ''[[wikt:praat#Dutch|"talk"]]'') is a [[free software|free]] [[computer software]] package for the scientific [[Voice analysis|analysis]] of [[Speech communication|speech]] in [[phonetics]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fon.hum.uva.nl/praat/ |title=Praat: doing phonetics by computer |accessdate=2017-09-20}}</ref> It was designed, and continues to be developed, by [[Paul Boersma]] and [[David Weenink]] of the [[University of Amsterdam]]. It can run on a wide range of [[operating system]]s, including various versions of [[Unix]], [[Linux]], [[Mac OS|Mac]] and [[Microsoft Windows]] (2000, XP, Vista, 7, 8, 10). The program supports [[speech synthesis]], including [[articulatory synthesis]].
