{{Unreferenced|date=December 2006}}
{{italic title}}
[[Image:Mitchellandwebb.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Webb and Mitchell as Sir Digby Chicken-Caesar and Ginger during the live stage show.]]
'''''The Two Faces of Mitchell and Webb''''' was a live stage tour undertaken by the comedy team of [[David Mitchell (comedian)|David Mitchell]] and [[Robert Webb]], accompanied by their frequent collaborators [[James Bachman]] and [[Abigail Burdess]], who played supporting roles.

==Overview==
The show toured forty-four venues in the UK between October and December 2006.  The content of the tour was adapted by Mitchell, Webb, and director [[Nick Morris]] from material previously generated by the team, particularly the sketch shows ''[[That Mitchell and Webb Look]]'' and ''[[That Mitchell and Webb Sound]]'', with significant focus placed on recurring sketches and characters. These included Ted and Peter, [[Numberwang]], The Party Planners, Big Talk, The Surprising Adventures of Sir Digby Chicken-Caesar, The Honeymoon's Over and The Lazy Film Writers.

==DVD release==
The date at the [[Grand Opera House (York)|Grand Opera House]] in [[York]] on 27 October 2006 was filmed for a [[DVD]] release, which was released in the UK (Region 2) on 27 November 2006 by [[Universal Studios|Universal]].  The disc included a [[teaser trailer]] for the film ''[[Magicians (2007 film)|Magicians]]'', in which both Mitchell and Webb starred.

